\fs24 \cf0 \strokec2 PREDICT (OSCARS)
\f1\b0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 Within the OSCARS-funded 
\f0\b \strokec2 PREDICT
\f1\b0 \strokec2  project, led by 
\f0\b \strokec2 Maria Paniw (CSIC)
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , I contribute to the development of an open and interoperable cyberinfrastructure for ecological forecasting, coordinated through 
\f0\b \strokec2 LifeWatch ERIC
\f1\b0 \strokec2 . I work within a multidisciplinary team including 
\f0\b \strokec2 Owen Petchey
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , 
\f0\b \strokec2 Emily Simmonds
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , 
\f0\b \strokec2 Thomas F. Johnson
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , 
\f0\b \strokec2 Gerbrand Koren
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , 
\f0\b \strokec2 Cara Gallagher
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , 
\f0\b \strokec2 Melina Kourantidou
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , 
\f0\b \strokec2 Patricia Singh
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , 
\f0\b \strokec2 \uc0\u304 stem Fer
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , 
\f0\b \strokec2 Iestyn Woolway
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , and 
\f0\b \strokec2 Marco Baity Jesi
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , among others. My contributions focus on developing a temporal and spatial forecasting challenge through fully open source plant functional traits data in European Alps. \

\f0\b \strokec2 Do\'f1ana vegetation forecasting challenge
\f1\b0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 I contribute to forecasting vegetation dynamics in the Do\'f1ana National Park through the Do\'f1ana Digital Twin platform led my Maria Paniw (CSIC). This work focuses on near-term forecasts of vegetation change and on evaluating how environmental drivers and model structure affect predictive performance. The first version of this infrastructure is now available. GIVE LINK: https://donanadt.lifewatch.dev/app/forecasting-vegetation-dynamics \

\f0\b \strokec2 European ecological forecasting database
\f1\b0 \strokec2 \uc0\u8232 As part of the 
\f0\b \strokec2 European Ecological Forecasting Initiative (EEFI) Steering Committee
\f1\b0 \strokec2 , I contribute to building a comprehensive database of ecological forecasts in Europe. The database documents ongoing and completed forecasting efforts, including forecast targets, data sources, modeling approaches, and evaluation practices. Its aim is to map the current landscape of ecological forecasting in Europe and to identify patterns, gaps, and opportunities for advancing predictability across systems. Explore the database GIVE THE LINK: https://euro-ecoforecast.wordpress.com/forecasting-applications-database/\cf3 \strokec3 \
